  "2026-07-07T11:22:51.500Z",codex-agent,"Evidence update: addressed fresh PR review feedback before repush. Cubic P1 runtime exposure fixed by moving ExtensionApiRegistrar internals to ECMAScript private fields with regression coverage proving legacy internal field names are not exposed to extension activators. Gemini command-trace feedback addressed by recording invalid override/run-handler values and metadata validation reasons in registerCommand traces. Malformed policy override names now render safely and are covered. Verification: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/extensions/extension-loader-internal.spec.ts (4 passed); node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/extensions/extension-command.spec.ts tests/unit/extensions/extension-loader.spec.ts (224 passed); pnpm quality:static passed; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed with 5450 tests and 100/100/100/100. Preliminary Greptile review 494e48d7 was clean but excluded uncommitted files, so final Greptile will rerun after amend."
  "2026-07-07T11:29:19.451Z",codex-agent,"Evidence update: amended and force-pushed PR #479 head 124499495b07f38df32d5ec971d3bd0f94ac4f89 after fresh bot feedback fixes. Final committed-head Greptile review b5c75b05-89c7-4235-b816-240838b9a526 reported confidence 5/5 with no comments. Re-triggered @greptileai, /gemini review, and @coderabbitai full review in PR comment 4903270052; awaiting GitHub checks and bot responses on the new head."
  "2026-07-07T11:57:32.720Z",codex-agent,"Evidence update: addressed fresh CodeRabbit and Gemini review feedback after head 12449949. Removed public CHANGELOG.md link to internal .agents/pm tracker path in favor of GitHub issue #467, added schema.flags policy enforcement for inline registerCommand definition flags with regression coverage, and made doctor policy detail rendering defensive for null/undefined policy blocks without adding private core imports. Verification: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/extensions/extension-command.spec.ts tests/unit/extensions/extension-loader.spec.ts (225 passed); pnpm quality:static passed; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed with 5451 tests and 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-07T12:02:49.551Z",codex-agent,"Evidence update: amended and force-pushed PR #479 head 03700d1d14e07e02cb95d41af68e62960a1bbc02 after CodeRabbit/Gemini follow-up fixes. Final committed-head Greptile review 045f951c-3bae-4bbf-8449-410879b317c6 reported confidence 5/5 with no comments. Re-triggered @greptileai, /gemini review, and @coderabbitai full review in PR comment 4903559615; awaiting GitHub checks and bot responses on the new head."
  "2026-07-07T12:12:18.165Z",codex-agent,"Evidence update: restored CHANGELOG.md to the package-owned pm-changelog generated item link after CI Gates (static) failed on pnpm changelog:pm:check. Local pnpm changelog:pm:check now passes with pm-changelog 2026.7.6. CodeRabbit's request for a public GitHub issue link is valid UX feedback, but in this repo the generated changelog contract currently derives links from --item-url-base https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/blob/main/.agents/pm; changing the generated line inside pm-cli breaks the mandatory package-owned changelog gate. If we want public issue labels/links in generated output, that belongs as an upstream pm-changelog option rather than a hand edit here."
  "2026-07-07T12:35:06.378Z",codex-agent,"Evidence update: addressed Gemini's partial-policy fallback feedback on PR #479. buildExtensionPolicyDetails now defaults missing mode/trust_mode scalar values when extensions.policy is partial, while preserving configured scalar values and normalized lists. Added regression coverage for mode-only and trust_mode-only partial policy objects. Verification: focused extension helper test passed; full extension command/loader slice passed (225 tests); pnpm quality:static passed; pnpm changelog:pm:check passed with pm-changelog 2026.7.6; full node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed with 5451 tests and 100/100/100/100."
