docs[2]{path,scope,note}:
  docs/EXTENSIONS.md,project,package smoke-test isolation guidance
  docs/SDK.md,project,package author isolated doctor guidance
close_reason: "Implemented isolated package/extension doctor diagnostics for GH-467: --isolated/--ignore-global skips global registrations, package doctor help documents the PM_GLOBAL_PATH recipe, project diagnostics surface global-leak metadata/remediation, SDK/action/tool contracts and completions advertise the flags, and temp-dir dogfood plus full coverage/health/changelog/security checks passed."
body: "GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/467\n\n## Problem\n`pm package doctor --project --json --detail deep` in a temporary workspace reported global extension renderer overrides from the developer machine (`extension_output_renderer_override_global:json:global:pm-ops`), breaking an otherwise hermetic pm-changelog package smoke test until every pm subprocess set `PM_GLOBAL_PATH` to a temp dir.\n\n## Why it matters\nAgents/CI create temp workspaces to test package installation; global state leaking into project-scoped diagnostics makes tests machine-dependent and expensive to debug. The workaround is discoverable only if the agent already knows PM_GLOBAL_PATH exists.\n\n## Proposed fix\n- `pm package doctor --project --ignore-global` (or `--isolated`) mode.\n- Document the PM_GLOBAL_PATH recipe in `doctor --help --explain`.\n- Emit an isolation hint in diagnostics whenever global-scope registrations are present in project results.\n\nRelated: pm-qt5d (project install with --pm-path writes extensions into caller workspace — same context-boundary family, opposite direction)."
